The LEAP (Leadership Expression Assessment Profile) instrument is the
exclusive intellectual property of Mentor Success Academy. Unauthorized
reproduction or distribution is strictly prohibited.

---

## What this is
A Node.js/Express web app that delivers the LEAP — Leadership Expression
Assessment Profile — a 72-statement self-assessment that reveals an individual's
natural leadership expression across four core types and twelve blends.

Results are stored server-side in a JSON file that persists across sessions
and devices. All quiz takers share the same database, so admins see every
result regardless of which device or browser the participant used.

The app also keeps a local-storage backup for offline resilience and migrates
older SELCS records (from version 1) automatically the first time they load.

---

## Files
```
leap-quiz/
├── server.js           ← Express backend + all API routes
├── package.json        ← Dependencies
├── render.yaml         ← Render deployment config
├── data/
│   └── results.json    ← Created automatically on first run
└── public/
    └── index.html      ← Full frontend (quiz, review, admin, about)
```

---

## Naming history

This app was originally launched as the **SELCS Quiz** (Social Emotional
Leadership Communication Style). In May 2026 it was renamed to **LEAP**
(Leadership Expression Assessment Profile) to better reflect the instrument's
focus on natural leadership expression rather than communication style alone.

The four core types — Driver, Inspirer, Sustainer, Cultivator — and the twelve
blended profiles are unchanged. Existing results from the SELCS era remain
fully accessible and the front-end will load them seamlessly via the legacy
localStorage key on first visit.

---

## Deploy to Render

### Step 1 — Push to GitHub
1. Create a new GitHub repo: `leap-quiz` (or rename the existing `selcs-quiz` repo)
2. Replace all files at the repo root with the new ones from this package
3. Make sure `public/index.html` and `server.js` are at the root level

### Step 2 — If renaming the existing Render service
1. Open the existing `selcs-quiz` service in Render
2. Settings → rename to `leap-quiz`
3. The URL changes from `selcs-quiz.onrender.com` to `leap-quiz.onrender.com`
4. Render will redeploy automatically when you push the new code

### Step 2 (alternative) — Creating a fresh service
1. Go to https://dashboard.render.com → New → Web Service
2. Connect your GitHub repo `leap-quiz`
3. Settings:
   - **Name:** leap-quiz
   - **Build Command:** `npm install`
   - **Start Command:** `node server.js`
   - **Instance Type:** Free (or Starter for always-on)

### Step 3 — Persistent disk (IMPORTANT)
Without this, results.json resets every time Render restarts.

1. In your Render service → Disks → Add Disk
2. **Name:** leap-data
3. **Mount Path:** `/opt/render/project/src/data`
4. **Size:** 1 GB (free tier)

If you're renaming an existing service, the existing `selcs-data` disk can be
kept as-is — the data inside is portable. Render will continue to mount it at
the same path.

### Step 4 — Environment variable
Set in Render → Environment:

- `ADMIN_PASSWORD` = (your chosen secure password)

The legacy variable `SELCS_ADMIN_PASSWORD` still works as a fallback for one
release, but please update to `ADMIN_PASSWORD` at your earliest convenience.

### Step 5 — Update the MSA Platform
The MSA Platform's mentor and mentee dashboards link to the LEAP quiz.
After the rename, update the link in:

- `public/mentor-home.html` (one occurrence)
- `public/mentee-home.html` (one occurrence)

Change `https://selcs-quiz.onrender.com/` to the new URL.

---

## Admin Access
- Open the **All Records** tab
- Enter your admin password (set in Render environment variables as `ADMIN_PASSWORD`)
- View every result, grouped by organization
- Filter by organization
- Export all results as a CSV spreadsheet (`LEAP_Results.csv`)
- Delete individual records if needed

---

## Local Development
```bash
cd leap-quiz
npm install
node server.js
# Open http://localhost:3000
```

